      "content": "being \"honest\" with myself just confirms that i've ruined everything. my family, my reputation, my life... it's all a wreckage now. every time i close my eyes i just see the spreadsheets and the look on my parents' faces. it's not just a mistake, it's a permanent stain. i feel like the world would actually just move on without me, and the shame would finally stop being so loud. it feels like the only logical way to solve the problem of the shame is to just end the person who feels it.",
